data.name: lblNumberDescription.HelpText
data.value:
This is the telephone number CallButler will call when this department is selected.
This phone number should include all country and area codes. You may or may not include punctuation. Examples of valid numbers are: 1-555-1234 and 15551234
Note: For CallButler for Skype editions, this number may also be a Skype Name.

data.name: wizardHeader3.Description
data.value: Specify a number to which to transfer the call

data.name: smoothLabel1.HelpText
data.value:
Specify a path to a custom script file. CallButler will execute this custom script when this department is selected.
Please note that if you are managing a CallButler service on another computer, you will need to specify a path to a script that is saved on that computer.

data.name: smoothLabel2.HelpText
data.value: Specify a name for this department here. The name you give this department is for your reference only and will not have any affect on what the caller hears.

data.name: lblDepartmentName.HelpText
data.value: Specify a name for this department here. The name you give this department is for your reference only and will not have any affect on what the caller hears.

data.name: lblAddon.HelpText
data.value:
Use this if you want to run an add-on module.
You can select the add-on module by pressing the Next button below.

data.name: lblScript.HelpText
data.value:
Use this if you want to run a custom-built script when this department is selected. With a custom script you can create your own call flows and even interface with databases and other applications.
To create a custom script you may want to use the inTeliScript editor included with CallButler. See the CallButler documentation for information on creating and using custom scripts.
You can browse for a custom script by pressing the Next button below.

data.name: lblScript.Text
data.value: Run a custom script (For advanced users)

data.name: lblNumber.HelpText
data.value:
Use this if you want to transfer the caller to another telephone number when this department is selected.
You might use this type of department to:
- Transfer callers to a fax machine - Transfer callers to another company or division
You can specify a telephone number by pressing the Next button below.
Note: CallButler for Skype Edition users may also transfer the caller to a Skype Name.

data.name: lblNumber.HelpTitle
data.value: Transfer the Call to a Telephone Number

data.name: lblExtension.HelpText
data.value:
Use this if you want to transfer the caller to a specific extension when this department is selected.
You might use this type of department to:
- Transfer callers wanting to talk to someone in sales to your sales manager's extension - Transfer callers to an extension with a voicemail box used for general messages
You can specify a specific extension by pressing the Next button below.

data.name: lblExtension.HelpTitle
data.value: Transfer the Call to an Extension

data.name: lblExtension.Text
data.value: Transfer the call to an extension

data.name: lblMessage.HelpText
data.value:
Use this if you want to play a pre-recorded message to callers when this department is selected.
You might use this type of department for:
- Store hours and directions - Monthly specials - Listing of products and services
You can record a new message or select an exising sound for the message by pressing the Next button below.
